<item>
            <title>[MRUNIT-188] Throw assertion error if drivers are reused</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MRUNIT-188</link>
                <project id="12311292" key="MRUNIT">MRUnit</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We should throw an assertion error if a driver.run method is called more than once. See &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MRUNIT-187&quot; title=&quot;previous outputs not cleared by ReduceDriver.run()&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MRUNIT-187&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MRUNIT-187&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for more details.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12650810">MRUNIT-188</key>
            <summary>Throw assertion error if drivers are reused</summary>
